bular features, as well as axillary nodal and osseous metastases.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190090&amp;id=fig4c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig4d" class="graphic" aria-label="(a) MLO diagnostic mammographic view in a 58-year-old woman with no prior history of surgery shows left nipple retraction and a retroareolar spiculated mass (circle) with axillary lymphadenopathy (arrow). (b) CC magnification view of the retroareolar region shows associated pleomorphic calcifications (arrow). (c) Radial US image shows a corresponding suspicious mass (arrow). (d, e) MLO mammographic view (d) shows that in retrospect, asymmetric left nipple retraction and focal asymmetry (circle; CC view not shown) were present 5 years previously, when compared to the right breast and nipple depicted on the MLO mammographic view (e). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 1, ER- and PR-positive, HER2-negative, 2.9-cm IDC with ductal and lobular features, as well as axillary nodal and osseous metastases."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190090/asset/images/large/rg.2020190090.fig4d.jpeg" height="1413" width="919" aria-labelledby="fig4d" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4d</span>. <b>(a)</b> MLO diagnostic mammographic view in a 58-year-old woman with no prior history of surgery shows left nipple retraction and a retroareolar spiculated mass (circle) with axillary lymphadenopathy (arrow). <b>(b)</b> CC magnification view of the retroareolar region shows associated pleomorphic calcifications (arrow). <b>(c)</b> Radial US image shows a corresponding suspicious mass (arrow). <b>(d, e)</b> MLO mammographic view <b>(d)</b> shows that in retrospect, asymmetric left nipple retraction and focal asymmetry (circle; CC view not shown) were present 5 years previously, when compared to the right breast and nipple depicted on the MLO mammographic view <b>(e)</b>. Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 1, ER- and PR-positive, HER2-negative, 2.9-cm IDC with ductal and lobular features, as well as axillary nodal and osseous metastases.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190090&amp;id=fig4d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig4e" class="graphic" aria-label="(a) MLO diagnostic mammographic view in a 58-year-old woman with no prior history of surgery shows left nipple retraction and a retroareolar spiculated mass (circle) with axillary lymphadenopathy (arrow). (b) CC magnification view of the retroareolar region shows associated pleomorphic calcifications (arrow). (c) Radial US image shows a corresponding suspicious mass (arrow). (d, e) MLO mammographic view (d) shows that in retrospect, asymmetric left nipple retraction and focal asymmetry (circle; CC view not shown) were present 5 years previously, when compared to the right breast and nipple depicted on the MLO mammographic view (e). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 1, ER- and PR-positive, HER2-negative, 2.9-cm IDC with ductal and lobular features, as well as axillary nodal and osseous metastases."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190090/asset/images/large/rg.2020190090.fig4e.jpeg" height="1413" width="919" aria-labelledby="fig4e" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4e</span>. <b>(a)</b> MLO diagnostic mammographic view in a 58-year-old woman with no prior history of surgery shows left nipple retraction and a retroareolar spiculated mass (circle) with axillary lymphadenopathy (arrow). <b>(b)</b> CC magnification view of the retroareolar region shows associated pleomorphic calcifications (arrow). <b>(c)</b> Radial US image shows a corresponding suspicious mass (arrow). <b>(d, e)</b> MLO mammographic view <b>(d)</b> shows that in retrospect, asymmetric left nipple retraction and focal asymmetry (circle; CC view not shown) were present 5 years previously, when compared to the right breast and nipple depicted on the MLO mammographic view <b>(e)</b>. Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 1, ER- and PR-positive, HER2-negative, 2.9-cm IDC with ductal and lobular features, as well as axillary nodal and osseous metastases.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190090&amp;id=fig4e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig5a" class="graphic" aria-label="(a, b) MLO (a) and CC (b) screening mammographic views in a 73-year-old woman show a 3-o’clock–position posterior depth focal asymmetry (arrow in b) in the retroglandular clear space (no-man’s- land) of the right breast. (c) Transverse US image shows a corresponding suspicious mass (arrow). (d) Contrast-enhanced maximal intensity projection MR image shows extensive multicentric disease (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed grade 1, ER- and PR-positive, HER2-negative, stage T3, N0M0 ILC."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190090/asset/images/large/rg.2020190090.fig5a.jpeg" height="1725" width="1105" aria-labelledby="fig5a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5a</span>. <b>(a, b)</b> MLO <b>(a)</b> and CC <b>(b)</b> screening mammographic views in a 73-year-old woman show a 3-o’clock–position posterior depth focal asymmetry (arrow in <b>b</b>) in the retroglandular clear space (no-man’s- land) of the right breast. <b>(c)</b> Transverse US image shows a corresponding suspicious mass (arrow). <b>(d)</b> Contrast-enhanced maximal intensity projection MR image shows extensive multicentric disease (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed grade 1, ER- and PR-positive, HER2-negative, stage T3, N0M0 ILC.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figur