. Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 2–3, ER-positive, PR-negative, HER2-negative, multifocal stage T1c (1.3-cm) N1a intramammary node, M0 IDC."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190090/asset/images/large/rg.2020190090.fig9g.jpeg" height="704" width="1433" aria-labelledby="fig9g" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9g</span>. <b>(a–f)</b> Multiple MLO <b>(a–c)</b> and CC <b>(d–f)</b> screening mammographic views obtained in 2011 <b>(a, d)</b>, 2014 <b>(b, e)</b>, and 2018 <b>(c, f)</b> in a 74-year-old woman show a relatively stable focal asymmetry (arrow) in the right breast at the 9-o’clock position, posterior depth. <b>(g)</b> Transverse US image shows a corresponding irregular mass (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 2–3, ER-positive, PR-negative, HER2-negative, multifocal stage T1c (1.3-cm) N1a intramammary node, M0 IDC.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190090&amp;id=fig9g">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10a" class="graphic" aria-label="(a) CC diagnostic mammographic view in a 30-year-old woman with a palpable area of concern, demarcated by a skin BB marker, demonstrates a right breast mass (arrow) near the 3-o’clock-position, anterior depth. (b) Corresponding transverse US image shows an oval mass (arrow), which was believed to represent a fibroadenoma and categorized as a BI-RADS 3 lesion. (c, d) Follow-up CC mammographic view (c) and transverse US image (d) obtained 6 months later show an enlarging mass (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 3, ER-positive, PR-negative, HER2-negative, 3.4-cm N0M0 IDC."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190090/asset/images/large/rg.2020190090.fig10a.jpeg" height="2232" width="1122" aria-labelledby="fig10a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10a</span>. <b>(a)</b> CC diagnostic mammographic view in a 30-year-old woman with a palpable area of concern, demarcated by a skin BB marker, demonstrates a right breast mass (arrow) near the 3-o’clock-position, anterior depth. <b>(b)</b> Corresponding transverse US image shows an oval mass (arrow), which was believed to represent a fibroadenoma and categorized as a BI-RADS 3 lesion. <b>(c, d)</b> Follow-up CC mammographic view <b>(c)</b> and transverse US image <b>(d)</b> obtained 6 months later show an enlarging mass (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 3, ER-positive, PR-negative, HER2-negative, 3.4-cm N0M0 IDC.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190090&amp;id=fig10a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10b" class="graphic" aria-label="(a) CC diagnostic mammographic view in a 30-year-old woman with a palpable area of concern, demarcated by a skin BB marker, demonstrates a right breast mass (arrow) near the 3-o’clock-position, anterior depth. (b) Corresponding transverse US image shows an oval mass (arrow), which was believed to represent a fibroadenoma and categorized as a BI-RADS 3 lesion. (c, d) Follow-up CC mammographic view (c) and transverse US image (d) obtained 6 months later show an enlarging mass (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 3, ER-positive, PR-negative, HER2-negative, 3.4-cm N0M0 IDC."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190090/asset/images/large/rg.2020190090.fig10b.jpeg" height="1003" width="1683" aria-labelledby="fig10b" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10b</span>. <b>(a)</b> CC diagnostic mammographic view in a 30-year-old woman with a palpable area of concern, demarcated by a skin BB marker, demonstrates a right breast mass (arrow) near the 3-o’clock-position, anterior depth. <b>(b)</b> Corresponding transverse US image shows an oval mass (arrow), which was believed to represent a fibroadenoma and categorized as a BI-RADS 3 lesion. <b>(c, d)</b> Follow-up CC mammographic view <b>(c)</b> and transverse US image <b>(d)</b> obtained 6 months later show an enlarging mass (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 3, ER-positive, PR-negative, HER2-negative, 3.4-cm N0M0 IDC.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190090&amp;id=fig10b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10c" class="graphic" aria-label="(a) CC diagnostic mammographic view in a 30-year-old woman with a palpable area of concern, demarcated by a skin BB marker, demonstrates a right breast mass (arrow) near the 3-o’clock-position, anterior depth. (b) Corresponding transverse US image shows an oval mass (arrow), which was believed to represent a fibroadenoma and categorized as a BI-RADS 3 lesion. (c, d) Follow-up CC mammographic view (c) and transverse US image (d) obtained 6 months later show an enlarging mass (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 3, ER-positive, PR-negative, HER2-negative, 3.4-cm N0M0 IDC."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190090/asset/images/large/rg.2020190090.fig10c.jpeg" height="2232" width="1125" aria-labelledby="fig10c" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10c</span>. <b>(a)</b> CC diagnostic mammographic view in a 30-year-old woman with a palpable area of concern, demarcated by a skin BB marker, demonstrates a right breast mass (arrow) near the 3-o’clock-position, anterior depth. <b>(b)</b> Corresponding transverse US image shows an oval mass (arrow), which was believed to represent a fibroadenoma and categorized as a BI-RADS 3 lesion. <b>(c, d)</b> Follow-up CC mammographic view <b>(c)</b> and transverse US image <b>(d)</b> obtained 6 months later show an enlarging mass (arrow). Histopathologic analysis revealed a grade 3, ER-positive, PR-negat