wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic" aria-label="(a–d) MLO (a, b) and CC (c, d) screening mammographic views in a 73-year-old woman demonstrate a left breast medial asymmetry (arrow in d), middle depth, seen in retrospect, with right MLO (a) and CC (c) screening mammographic views provided for comparison. (e, f) MLO (e) and CC (f) screening mammographic views obtained 3 years later demonstrate increased conspicuity of the now focal asymmetry (arrow) in the upper inner quadrant, posterior depth, of the left breast. (g) Corresponding transverse US image shows a corresponding suspicious mass (calipers). Histopathologic analysis revealed grade 3, ER- and PR-positive, HER2-negative, stage T2 (3.1-cm) N3aM0 ILC."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020190090/asset/images/large/rg.2020190090.fig11a.jpeg" height="2112" width="811" aria-labelledby="fig11a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span>. <b>(a–d)</b> MLO <b>(a, b)</b> and CC <b>(c, d)</b> screening mammographic views in a 73-year-old woman demonstrate a left breast medial asymmetry (arrow in <b>d</b>), middle depth, seen in retrospect, with right MLO <b>(a)</b> and CC <b>(c)</b> screening mammographic views provided for comparison. <b>(e, f)</b> MLO <b>(e)</b> and CC <b>(f)</b> screening mammographic views obtained 3 years later demonstrate increased conspicuity of the now focal asymmetry (arrow) in the upper inner quadrant, posterior depth, of the left breast. <b>(g)</b> Corresponding transverse US image shows a corresponding suspicious mass (calipers). Histopathologic analysis revealed grade 3, ER- and PR-positive, HER2-negative, stage T2 (3.1-cm) N3aM0 ILC.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020190090&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic" aria-label="(a–d) MLO (a, b) and CC (c, d) screening